oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Amputation of Prolapsed Cervical Rings
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Heider, Lawrence E.
Tharp, Vernon L.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The cow's cervix is normally two to four inches in length and three-fourths to two and three fourths in diameter. The cervix in a heifer may be smaller than the minimum size given for cows. As a cow increases in the number of parturitions and in age, the size of her cervix usually increases. The size of the cervix in aged cows may exceed the dimensions listed, especially in regard to diameter.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1973; 34-35
